&lt;p&gt;Guidelight Health provides insurance-based intermediate levels of care that are structured, transformative, personalized and accessible. Guidelight is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We&#39;re passionate about fostering an environment where everyone, irrespective of their race, gender, sexual orientation, or background, feels valued and included.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Manager of Clinical Outreach, you&#39;ll be Guidelight&#39;s ambassador across Greater Boston, building the relationships and community partnerships that help more people access high-quality mental health care when they need it most. Reporting to the Senior Director, Clinical Outreach, you&#39;ll play a key role in expanding Guidelight&#39;s presence in the market and shaping how we show up for providers, patients, and communities. This is an opportunity to have a direct impact on our growth and mission. You&#39;ll partner closely with operations and clinical leaders to develop and execute a market outreach strategy, identify and cultivate referral partnerships, and create seamless pathways for patients to connect with Guidelight&#39;s programs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Guidelight, we believe mental healthcare works best when communities are connected. We strive to be more than a provider. We aim to be a trusted partner and resource hub for the local mental health ecosystem. Whether you&#39;re meeting with therapists, hospitals, schools, primary care providers, or community organizations, you&#39;ll help strengthen the network of support that leads to better outcomes for patients and families. If you love building relationships, creating opportunities, and making a meaningful impact in your community, this role offers a chance to help shape the future of mental healthcare in Greater Boston.&lt;/p&gt;
